{
  "texts": [
    "In summary, LLMs not only learn from experience in a manner akin to humans, but their characteristics of emergence and homogenization also share analogous moral functions with Dewey's concept of habit.",
    "The pre-training phase enables LLMs to acquire natural language abilities and human social cognition, but issues such as generating discriminatory language and failing to recognize prompts that induce harmful speech still persist.",
    "To address these issues, ChatGPT, based on GPT-3 (Brown et al., 2020), adopts the RLHF training method (Knox & Stone, 2011; Ouyang et al., 2022), and integrates training with human-provided ethical values to become more helpful, honest, and harmless (Bai et al., 2022).",
    "RLHF corresponds to the second stage of human moral growth: the reconstruction of habits with the involvement of intelligence and impulse.",
    "In human moral learning, rewards and punishments (particularly punishments) can inhibit the original habitual action and prevent it from being automatically executed according to the original pattern, thus forming new habits through reinforcement learning."
  ]
}